                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/9–2540: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-25T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 25, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>223. Please ascertain from Colonel Christian and Captain Brereton whether any
                    mention was made during the staff conversations at Asuncion of the possibility
                    of Paraguay according aviation bases to the United States. If such mention was
                    made please report fully by rush telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
